Soccer lovers were treated to the ultimate watch and play night football experience on December 13 at Halycon Lounge and Grill, Kitengela. The event started at 5pm and lasted late into the night. Revellers watched performances in addition to live football matches as the four regional winners battled to become the first champions of Guinness Night Football and a direct ticket to Lagos, Nigeria, for the Pan-African championship. Artists who performed included Samido, Boondocks Gang, Ethic, Lavosti Band and Khaligraph Jones. The event followed similar successful Night Football events in Kisumu, Machakos and Nakuru.